  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with the APOE-ε4 genotype are at increased risk of both vascular dementia and
      peripheral vascular disease. Patients undergoing major vascular surgery are at particularly
      high risk of delirium and other, more subtle, changes in cognitive function following
      surgery. The hypothesis of this trial is that the APOE-ε4 genotype is associated with both
      delirium and postoperative cognitive dysfunction (POCD).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
